OL,3,CIsle of Man set to take historic step
OL,4,Ccloser to legalising assisted dying
OL,6,FThe phrase "assisted dying", and the
OL,7,Flanguage used, varies depending on
OL,8,Feither side of the debate.
OL,10,FDignity in Dying, a pro-change
OL,11,Fcampaign group, say that assisted
OL,12,Fdying allows a person with a terminal
OL,13,Fcondition the choice to control their
OL,14,Fdeath if they decide their suffering
OL,15,Fis unbearable.
OL,17,FThey argue that, along with good care,
OL,18,Fdying people who are terminally ill
OL,19,Fand mentally competent adults deserve
OL,20,Fthe choice to control the timing and
OL,21,Fmanner of their death.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
