OL,3,CIsle of Man set to take historic step
OL,4,Ccloser to legalising assisted dying
OL,6,FBut the campaign group Care Not
OL,7,FKilling, who oppose the idea, uses the
OL,8,Fterms "assisted suicide" and
OL,9,F"euthanasia", and argues that the
OL,10,Ffocus should be on "promoting more and
OL,11,Fbetter palliative care" rather than
OL,12,Fany law change.
OL,14,FThey say legalising assisted dying, as
OL,15,Fproposed in the new Bill, could "place
OL,16,Fpressure on vulnerable people to end
OL,17,Ftheir lives for fear of being a
OL,18,Ffinancial, emotional or care burden
OL,19,Fupon others".
